	abstract = {Deep learning methods have proven to be very effective for the task of image denoising even when clean reference images are not available. In particular, Noise2Noise, which requires pairs of noisy images during the training phase, has been shown to yield results as good as approaches using pairs of noisy and clean images (Noise2Clean). However, the performance of Noise2Noise drops when the amount of training data is reduced, limiting its capability in practical scenarios.},
